00:00:02.296 --> 00:00:06.288
Namaskar and welcome to nishamadhulika.com

00:00:06.744 --> 00:00:09.046
Today we will make papaya sabzi.

00:00:09.333 --> 00:00:14.007
Let's see what all ingrdients are required for making papaya sabzi.

00:00:14.382 --> 00:00:18.128
Raw papaya - 600 grams (2 small)

00:00:18.474 --> 00:00:26.092
Paste - 2 tomatoes, 1 inch ginger piece and 1-2 green chilies

00:00:26.949 --> 00:00:28.782
 Cumin seeds - 1/2 tsp

00:00:29.093 --> 00:00:30.212
Asafoetida - 1 pinch

00:00:30.631 --> 00:00:32.822
Turmeric powder - 1/2 tsp

00:00:33.188 --> 00:00:35.490
Coriander powder - 1 tsp

00:00:35.966 --> 00:00:39.530
Salt - 3/4 tsp (as per taste)

00:00:40.005 --> 00:00:43.204
Red chilly powder - less then 1/4 tsp

00:00:44.005 --> 00:00:47.323
Garam masala - less then 1/4 tsp

00:00:47.624 --> 00:00:50.720
Green coriander leaves - 1 tbsp (finely chopped)

00:00:51.029 --> 00:00:52.776
Oil - for making sabzi

00:00:54.672 --> 00:00:57.712
Firstly peel papaya and cut into pieces.

00:01:00.726 --> 00:01:04.123
Divide it into two parts and then peel it.

00:01:17.262 --> 00:01:20.960
Remove the seeds nicely like this.

00:01:24.957 --> 00:01:31.504
After cuting papaya rinse it thoroughly with water.

00:01:31.934 --> 00:01:37.093
Now make sabzi from the papaya.

00:01:37.474 --> 00:01:42.006
Add 1 tbsp oil in the heated pressure cooker.

00:01:48.411 --> 00:01:49.704
Also add asafoetid and cumin seeds.

00:01:56.736 --> 00:02:05.593
When cumin seeds become little brown in color add turmeric powder,

00:02:08.664 --> 00:02:10.268
and corriander powder.

00:02:15.592 --> 00:02:22.267
Now add tomato-ginger-green chilly paste into it.

00:02:28.274 --> 00:02:33.306
Saute the masala until oil floats on the surface.

00:02:34.038 --> 00:02:36.022
Masala is ready.

00:02:40.863 --> 00:02:47.886
Now add papaya pieces in the masala and cook nicely.

00:03:02.259 --> 00:03:07.910
Add salt and red chilly powder as well.

00:03:10.490 --> 00:03:20.942
Add red chily powder as per your taste or simply avoid it.

00:03:21.736 --> 00:03:30.648
Saute papaya pieces for two minutes so that they get coated nicely with the masala.

00:03:34.564 --> 00:03:39.223
Add little or 1/2 cup water in the cooker.

00:03:42.991 --> 00:03:44.182
Mix really well.

00:03:47.366 --> 00:03:48.708
Close the cooker with help of a lid.

00:03:52.664 --> 00:03:59.528
When it simmer's once, reduce the flame to minimum and cook for another 1-2 minutes.

00:04:08.425 --> 00:04:10.528
Sabzi is ready.

00:04:10.918 --> 00:04:14.300
Now add garam masala,

00:04:16.307 --> 00:04:18.068
and green coriander leaves in the sabzi.

00:04:18.870 --> 00:04:26.386
Add garam masala and corrinder leaves in the end so that their fragrance remains for long.

00:04:29.283 --> 00:04:37.379
This much quantity of sabzi can be served to 4-5 family members.

00:04:37.847 --> 00:04:43.950
Serve with chapatti, parantha, naan or rice.

00:04:44.363 --> 00:04:50.771
